xplr
Tags: file-managers, hackable

Hackable, minimal, fast TUI file explorer with scriptable behavior.

Important note:
xplr can print the working directory on exit, which makes it useful for shell workflows.

Help head:
USAGE:
    xplr [FLAG]... [OPTION]... [PATH] [SELECTION]...
--print-pwd-as-result    Prints the present working directory when quitting
--read-only              Enables read-only mode
--config <PATH>          Specifies a custom config file

> xplr --help
